<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2137" TARGET=_self>Racewar sever will be dumb</A> (Ghouldan)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> If they wanna improve Rping in the pvp server they do not have

<BR>&gt; to create this racewar server or aka ever-capture-the-flag.
<BR>&gt; Would they SHOULD do is change all the guards and vendors in all
<BR>&gt; the cities and make them semi realtic example... guards do only
<BR>&gt; maybe 12 a hit if they have a sword liek the rest of us, and
<BR>&gt; have them killable, I am sure the captain of the guard should be
<BR>&gt; tuff like level 40 maybe but normal guards should be like noraml
<BR>&gt; guards, maybe liek level 20, or even 15, vendors arent warriors
<BR>&gt; they should be weaker. WHAT THIS DOES? this allows dark races to
<BR>&gt; actually invade cities, all we can do now is lay siege stand
<BR>&gt; outside and stare at freeports pretty gates as the hummans run
<BR>&gt; to the saftey of the practically invincible guards protecting
<BR>&gt; them ( i think most guards are like level 30). that way we could
<BR>&gt; invade, and if humans dont protect their cityt then hey, maybe
<BR>&gt; all vendors which die wont respawn for like 2 real ife days or
<BR>&gt; something. that would be cool cause then we could invasions,
<BR>&gt; real ones ones with 100 orges charging freeport and actually
<BR>&gt; messing up the town, and human players actually HAVE to defend
<BR>&gt; instead of standing behind a guard and watching the pretty orges
<BR>&gt; stand on their asses.
<BR>&gt; just my two cents,
<BR>&gt; -Ghouldan
<P>I figure that vendors and guards should have a slower respawn rate. I feel that real life days is too much, but a game week would be just about right. Maybe even have it so that if the vendors get attacked too much, they hire a guard to protect them and even have to raise their prices. To keep it balanced, prices should go down and protection weaken in times of peace. That would be fair.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
